Once we have the mesh and the skeleton bind, the vertices of mesh now carry one more information, the skin weight, which is a measurement of how much a vertex is influenced by a certain joint. We see this by selecting the mesh, right click and select paint skin weight to open the paint skin weight tool.Â 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

A popular plugin called ng skin tool is a good alternative of the maya default tool. Many functions of ng skin tool are wrappers of the default ones, so we should be able to jump right in without any problem.
